    "searchText": "Feather supports the wallet choices presented by the application. On desktop, this may include MetaMask or Brave Wallet when their browser providers are available and authorized. Network identity Robinhood Chain uses ETH as its native gas currency. The application checks both the wallet network and its own configured network before enabling a transaction. If the two network identities disagree, Feather blocks execution. Switching the visible wallet chain alone is not enough when the configured runtime reports another chain. Account identity The connected address determines balances, approvals, positions, and transaction context. Changing accounts clears or reloads owner-specific state. A pending transaction remains associated with the account and chain that submitted it. You can browse documentation and public pool information without connecting. Connect only when an action needs your account or signature."
