    "searchText": "An imbalanced deposit that touches the active bin can pay a composition fee. This is separate from gas and swap fees. Before signing The review should identify the estimated composition fee, any protocol share, protected net placement, and each expected refund asset. Volatility or active-bin changes invalidate the estimate and require refresh. Native-asset refunds When native ETH is supplied to a wrapped-native pool, unused native-side value can cross the contract boundary as WETH. The receipt view must reconcile both ETH and WETH balances rather than claiming every unused amount returned as ETH. The confirmed transaction events and balance changes determine actual fees and refunds. A preflight value is an estimate based on the reviewed state."
